11/02/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Another miner died in the Bulqiza mine in central Albania. 
Njazi Alliu, 53, on Saturday (February 9th) became the 8th victim of conditions in the mine in the past year. 
The opposition reacted immediately, demanding the resignation of Economy and Energy Minister Genc Ruli, and insisting the government take responsibility for the fatalities. 
(GazetaShqiptare, Shekulli, Shqip - 10/02/08; Balkanweb, Top-Channel - 9/02/08)
